%br/

%h6.panel Let your customers know more about your company...

%dl.tabs{data: {tab: true}}
  %dd.active
    %a{href: "#panel2-1"} Optional information
  %dd
    %a{href: "#panel2-2"} Service provided
  %dd
    %a{href: "#panel2-3"} Upload Logo

.tabs-content

  #panel2-1.content.active
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        %p If you have a license number this will be added to your invoices.

    .row
      .small-12.medium-6.large-6.columns
        = f.label :license_number
        = f.text_field :license_number

    %br/

    .row
      .small-12.columns
        %p
          Let your customers know when you started your company. Your customers will see this on the About
          Company page.
    .row
      .small-12.medium-6.large-6.columns
        = f.label :established_on, 'Established on (yyyy-mm-dd)'
        = f.text_field :established_on, class: 'datePicker', placeholder: 'Date'

  #panel2-2.content
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        %p
          Tell EasyKeep what type of service you provide. That way when you create an invoice for your
          customers, instead of just saying "Services" over the services listed on the invoice, it will say
          "Cleaning Services" or "Lawn Care Services". Keep in mind that the word "Services" will be added after
          the type of service you provide.

    .row
      .small-12.medium-6.large-6.columns
        = f.label :service_provided
        .row.collapse
          .small-7.columns
            = f.text_field :service_provided
          .small-5.columns
            %span.postfix.radius Services

    %br/

    .row
      .small-12.columns
        %p
          Let your customers know what you and your company are all about. Your customers will see this on your
          About Company page.
        = f.label :service_summery
        = f.text_area :service_summery, placeholder: 'example: "Providing a service at a reasonable price..."'

  #panel2-3.content
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        %p
          Have a logo you'd like to show off? Then upload it for all to see. This will be displayed next to your
          company's name.

    .row
      .small-12.columns
        = f.label :logo do
          Upload your Logo
          \#{image_tag(f.object.logo_url) if f.object.logo?}
        = f.file_field :logo
        = f.label :remote_logo_url, 'or image URL'
        = f.text_field :remote_logo_url
        = f.hidden_field :logo_cache
        %label.checkbox
          = f.check_box :remove_logo
          Check box to remove Logo

%hr/
